data.Name: Mini Loading
data.Description: Mini loading refers to the application of a small or preliminary load to a sample, often used to precondition the material or to assess initial response characteristics before main loading.

data.Name: Mini Unloading
data.Description: Mini unloading involves the removal of the preliminary load applied during mini loading, used to observe the material's recovery and elastic properties after minor stress.

data.Name: Main Loading
data.Description: Main loading is the primary phase of applying significant stress or load to the sample, intended to test the material's behavior under expected operational conditions or to its failure point.

data.Name: Main Unloading
data.Description: Main unloading involves the removal of the main load, allowing for the assessment of residual strains, permanent deformations, or damage incurred during the main loading phase.
